    {
      "id": "1ae4750c-f3ba-80c9-8ac0-c28be95ebe14",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "DKT, while effective, is a much more data-driven approach than a knowledge-driven approach. However, its results tend to fluctuate due to not requiring elaborate representations of student knowledge. The authors find that DKT cannot properly establish long-term relationships and, to circumvent this issue, introduce a set of attention-based models. Benchmarking on 5 datasets shows that both models achieve state-of-the-art performance on KT tasks. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1ae4750c-f3ba-80c9-8ac0-c28be95ebe14",
        "parent": {
